# Flutter Agentic Template

Flutter/Dart project (web-first for Phase 1; iOS for later native retrofit; no Android). Source of truth: PM_PLAN.md, AGENT_HANDOFF.md; .cursor/skills/ (DEV_GUIDE, TEST_TDD, DESIGN_SYSTEM, techwriter, tester). Use techwriter for docs; use tester + .cursor/rules/testing.mdc for black-box, continuous tests. **New behavior:** Read TEST_TDD.md and tester skill first; write a failing test before production code (TDD). **Handoff:** When the user wants a handoff, run code review (code-reviewer), tech debt (tech-debt-evaluator), and `flutter test --coverage`; record in the handoff note. See AGENT_HANDOFF.md and .cursor/rules/handoff-checklist.mdc — do not skip.

**Non-Flutter work** (extensions, CLIs, other stacks): use the stack-agnostic [AgenticTemplate](https://github.com/pbuckles22/AgenticTemplate) repo — same agentic discipline without a Flutter scaffold.
